[{"id":42492,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"The nuclear reaction for the proton bombardment of Lithium is:<br><br>$^{7}_{3}\\text{Li} + ^{1}_{1}\\text{H} \\rightarrow 2 ^{4}_{2}\\text{He}$<br><br>The mass defect ($\\Delta m$) for the reaction is:<br><br>$\\Delta m = m(^{7}_{3}\\text{Li}) + m(^{1}_{1}\\text{H}) - 2m(^{4}_{2}\\text{He})$<br><br>$\\Delta m = 7.0183 + 1.008 - 2(4.004)$<br><br>$\\Delta m = 8.0263 - 8.008 = 0.0183 \\text{ u}$<br><br>Energy released per reaction ($Q$) is:<br><br>$Q = \\Delta m \\times 931 \\text{ MeV} = 0.0183 \\times 931 \\text{ MeV} = 17.0373 \\text{ MeV}$<br><br>Number of moles of $^{7}_{3}\\text{Li}$ in $\\dfrac{7}{17.13} \\text{ kg}$:<br><br>$n = \\dfrac{\\dfrac{7}{17.13} \\times 10^3 \\text{ g}}{7 \\text{ g/mol}} = \\dfrac{1000}{17.13} \\text{ mol}$<br><br>Number of atoms of $^{7}_{3}\\text{Li}$:<br><br>$N = n \\times N_A = \\dfrac{1000}{17.13} \\times 6.0 \\times 10^{23} = \\dfrac{6}{17.13} \\times 10^{26}$<br><br>Total energy released ($E$) is:<br><br>$E = N \\times Q = \\left(\\dfrac{6}{17.13} \\times 10^{26}\\right) \\times (17.0373 \\times 10^6 \\text{ eV})$<br><br>$E = \\dfrac{102.2238}{17.13} \\times 10^{32} \\text{ eV} \\approx 5.967 \\times 10^{32} \\text{ eV}$<br><br>Rounding to the nearest integer, we get $\\alpha = 6$.<br><br>Answer: $6$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42560,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>174</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>71</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>174</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>69</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>172</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>69</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>172</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>71</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Equivalent reaction can be written as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>-</mo></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>&#947;</mi></math></p><p>So, mass number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo></math>mass number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>182</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>174</mn></math></p><p>Atomic number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo></math>atomic number of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>74</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>71</mn></math></p><p>The reaction is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>D</mi><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>74</mn><mn>182</mn></mmultiscripts><munder><mo>&#10230;</mo><mi>&#945;</mi></munder><mmultiscripts><mi>D</mi><mn>1</mn><none></none><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>72</mn><mn>178</mn></mmultiscripts><munder><mo>&#10230;</mo><msup><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></munder><mmultiscripts><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn><none></none><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>73</mn><mn>178</mn></mmultiscripts><munder><mo>&#10230;</mo><mi>&#945;</mi></munder><mmultiscripts><mi>D</mi><mn>3</mn><none></none><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>71</mn><mn>174</mn></mmultiscripts><munder><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>&#947;</mi></munder><mmultiscripts><mi>D</mi><mn>4</mn><none></none><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>71</mn><mn>174</mn></mmultiscripts></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42603,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>208</mn><mo>;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn></math>","<math><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>208</mn><mo>;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn></math>","<math><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>81</mn></math>","<math><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>202</mn><mo>;</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>As we know that in alpha decay mass number reduced from for and the atomic number reduced by two</p><p>and in beta decay the mass number became unchange and atomic number increase from one</p><p>Change in <math><mi>Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math><br />Change in <math><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>TH</mi><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>90</mn><mn>232</mn></mmultiscripts><mtable><mtr><mtd><mover><mo>&#8594;</mo><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>&#945;</mi></mrow></mover></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn><mi>&#946;</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable><mi>&#160;</mi><mmultiscripts><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><none></none><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>82</mn><mn>208</mn></mmultiscripts></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42639,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["the rate of decay of radioactive source","the ability of a beam of gamma ray photons to produce ions in a target","the energy delivered by radiation to a target.","the biological effect of radiation"],"answer":3,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2006","image":null},{"id":42577,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#955;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>30</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>years</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42641,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["$6 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$9 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$18 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$12 \\mathrm{~mm}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Use I $=I_0 e^{-\\mu x}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":42594,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>nt</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ln</mi><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Slope</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow><msub><mi>t</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>&#955;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>B</mi></mfenced><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>C</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42582,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub></mover><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub></mover><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub></mover><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mover><mo>&#10230;</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub></mover><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp;days</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42512,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["in the same direction with same speed.","in opposite directions with the same speed.","in opposite directions with speed in the ratio of $2: 1$ respectively.","in opposite directions with speed in the ratio of $1: 2$ respectively."],"answer":3,"solution":"By conservation of momentum\n$\\begin{aligned}& \\mathrm{p}_{\\mathrm{i}}=\\mathrm{p}_{\\mathrm{f}} \\\\\n& \\mathrm{O}=\\mathrm{m}_1 \\mathrm{u}_{1+} \\mathrm{m}_2 \\mathrm{u}_2 \\\\& \\frac{\\mathrm{u}_1}{\\mathrm{u}_2}=-\\left[\\frac{1}{2}\\right] \\text { as } \\frac{\\mathrm{m}_1}{\\mathrm{~m}_2}=\\frac{2}{1}\n\\end{aligned}$\nmove in opposite direction with speed ratio $1: 2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42498,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{X}_{4}<\\mathrm{X}_{5}<\\mathrm{X}_{3}$","$\\mathrm{X}_{4}>\\mathrm{X}_{5}>\\mathrm{X}_{3}$","$\\mathrm{X}_{4}>\\mathrm{X}_{5}<\\mathrm{X}_{3}$","$\\mathrm{X}_{4}=\\mathrm{X}_{5}=\\mathrm{X}_{3}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$BE_{He^4} - BE_{He^3} = 20 MeV$ ...(1)<br>$BE_{He^5} - BE_{He^4} = -0.9 MeV$ ...(2)<br>From eq (1) & (2)<br>$BE_{He^4} > BE_{He^5} > BE_{He^3}$<br>$X_4 > X_5 > X_3$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42584,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Energy of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi></math> ray <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></math></p><p>Momentum of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi></math> ray <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></math><br />Total momentum is conserved.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>P</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mover><mi>P</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>Nu</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br />where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>P</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>Nu</mi></msub><mo>=</mo></math> momentum of decayed nuclei</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>Nu</mi></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>Nu</mi></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>KE</mi></math>&nbsp;of nuclei</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mfenced><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>Nu</mi></msub></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br />Loss in internal energy <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#947;</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>KE</mi><mi>Nu</mi></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42633,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{(M_o-8 M_p) C^2}$","$\\mathrm{(M_o-8 M_p-9 M_N) C^2}$","$\\mathrm{M_o C^2}$","$\\mathrm{(M_{\\mathrm{o}}-17 \\mathrm{M}_{\\mathrm{N}}) \\mathrm{C}^2}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Binding energy $=\\left(\\mathrm{M_o-8 M_P-9 M_N}\\right) \\mathrm{C^2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":42499,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Both Statement I and Statement II are true","Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Statement I is false but Statement II is true"],"answer":3,"solution":"Statement I is false because binding energy per nucleon does not increase monotonically with mass number. It peaks at Iron-56 and decreases for heavier elements.<br>Statement II is true. It describes the fundamental principle of nuclear reactions: fission of heavy nuclei (low BE/A) and fusion of light nuclei (low BE/A) both produce nuclei with higher binding energy per nucleon, releasing energy in the process. Both processes are energetically favorable for the same reason: moving toward higher stability (higher BE/A).","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42567,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Ratio of number of moles of substance&nbsp;in the beginning will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mi>A</mi></msub><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kg</mi></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kg</mi></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p><p>Number of half-life in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;for element&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p>Number of half-life in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;for element&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p>Hence, ratio of number of nuclei after&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced><msub><mi>n</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Thus, value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42559,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>min</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>063</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>At <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;disintegration rate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4250</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>dpm</mi></math></p><p>At <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></math>&nbsp;disintegration rate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2250</mn><mi>dpm</mi></math></p><p>The activity of a sample at any time&nbsp;is given by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>2250</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4250</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mfenced><mn>10</mn></mfenced></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfrac><mn>4250</mn><mn>2250</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>88</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>063</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42634,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["both the neutron number and the proton number change","there is no change in the proton number and the neutron number.","only the neutron number changes","only the proton number changes"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":42518,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["$10 \\mu \\mathrm{g}$","$20 \\mu \\mathrm{g}$","$0.2 \\mu \\mathrm{g}$","$2 \\mu \\mathrm{g}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\Delta \\mathrm{mc}^2=18 \\times 10^8 \\\\ & \\Delta \\mathrm{m} \\times 9 \\times 10^{16}=18 \\times 10^8 \\\\ & \\Delta \\mathrm{m}=2 \\times 10^{-8} \\mathrm{~kg}=20 \\mu \\mathrm{g}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42590,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>x</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>,</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn><mo>&#39;</mo></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>&#39;</mo></msubsup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>t</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42523,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Radius of a nucleus is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><msup><mi>A</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p><p>Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>∝</mo><mi>A</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>64</mn><mi>A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mn>64</mn><mrow><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mn>64</mn><mi>A</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>64</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1000</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>144</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow><mn>64</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>27</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42517,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["Electron","Neutron","$\\gamma$-radiations","Proton"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{Z} \\text { in LHS }=92 \\\\\n& \\mathrm{Z} \\text { in } \\mathrm{RHS}=56+36=92 \\\\\n& \\mathrm{~A} \\text { in } \\mathrm{LHS}=236 \\\\\n& \\mathrm{~A} \\text { in } \\mathrm{RHS}=141+92=233\n\\end{aligned}$<br />So 3 neutrons are released.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42615,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 97px; top: 37.6667px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 75px; top: 37.6667px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>16</mn></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 87px; top: 37.6667px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math><div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 59px; top: -5.77778px;\"><div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div></div>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math><br /><br />no. of nuclei of A decayed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>15</mn><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math><br /><br />no. of nuclei of B decayed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math><br /><br />required ratio <math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)","image":null},{"id":42553,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>120</mn></math> days","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>130</mn></math> days","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>180</mn></math> days","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> days"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given half life period of a radioactive substance is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>t</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn></math>&nbsp;days.</p><p>Here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>th</mi></math>&nbsp;of radioactive substance&nbsp;disintegrates means <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>th</mi></math>&nbsp;remains or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;half lives&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>days</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42497,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["$250 \\%$","$150 \\%$","$900 \\%$","$125 \\%$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Surface area $x \\propto A^{2/3}$<br>$X_i = 8^{2/3} K = 4K$<br>$X_f = (8 + 10 + 9)^{2/3} K = 9K$<br>% increase in surface area of nucleus<br>$x_i = \\dfrac{9K - 4K}{4K} \\times 100 = 125\\%$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42552,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Remaining amount of sample is<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Using radioactive decay law</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></msub></mfrac></msup></math></p><p>We&nbsp;have,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mfrac><mi>t</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></msub></mfrac></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>N</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p><p>Then,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>t</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p>Thus, half life of the sample is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>min</mi></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42653,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Nuclear Physics","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{N}_0 / 8$","$\\mathrm{N}_0 / 16$","$\\mathrm{N}_0 / 2$","$\\mathrm{N}_0 / 4$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Amount left $=N_0 / 2^n=N_0 / 8 \\quad($ Here $n=15 / 5=3)$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null}]